light markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="51">Super easy—I'll walk you through it step-by-step 👍</p>
<hr data-start="53" data-end="56">
<h1 data-section-id="z5b366" data-start="58" data-end="86">🖼️ STEP 1: Save the image</h1>
<p data-start="88" data-end="124">Since you uploaded it here, do this:</p>
<ol data-start="126" data-end="239">
<li data-section-id="1jsq5i7" data-start="126" data-end="189">
<p data-start="129" data-end="189"><strong data-start="129" data-end="154">Right-click the image</strong> (the cartoon electrician you sent)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="g57cv8" data-start="190" data-end="219">
<p data-start="193" data-end="219">Click <strong data-start="199" data-end="219">“Save image as…”</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="3ed5ie" data-start="220" data-end="239">
<p data-start="223" data-end="239">Name it exactly:</p>
</li>
</ol>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="241" data-end="259"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="contents"><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0e621efa.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>mascot.png</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<ol start="4" data-start="261" data-end="309">
<li data-section-id="x5lmjl" data-start="261" data-end="309">
<p data-start="264" data-end="309">Save it somewhere easy (like Desktop for now)</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="311" data-end="314">
<h1 data-section-id="12y7vra" data-start="316" data-end="370">📁 STEP 2: Put it in the same folder as your website</h1>
<p data-start="372" data-end="427">Now you need to move that image next to your HTML file.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="13ouq0f" data-start="429" data-end="455">Find your website file</h3>
<ul data-start="456" data-end="511">
<li data-section-id="5xn12c" data-start="456" data-end="511">
<p data-start="458" data-end="511">Wherever your <code data-start="472" data-end="479">.html</code> file is (example: <code data-start="498" data-end="510">index.html</code>)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="79xya3" data-start="513" data-end="522">Then:</h3>
<ol data-start="523" data-end="587">
<li data-section-id="10xnbl" data-start="523" data-end="542">
<p data-start="526" data-end="542">Open that folder</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="blxla8" data-start="543" data-end="587">
<p data-start="546" data-end="587">Drag <strong data-start="551" data-end="565">mascot.png</strong> into that same folder</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="589" data-end="592">
<h3 data-section-id="ojk4fb" data-start="594" data-end="625">✅ It should look like this:</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="627" data-end="675"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="contents"><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0e621efa.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>/your-folder</span><br><span>   index.html</span><br><span>   mascot.png</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="677" data-end="680">
<h1 data-section-id="6ttbkn" data-start="682" data-end="701">⚡ STEP 3: Test it</h1>
<ul data-start="703" data-end="762">
<li data-section-id="5srkau" data-start="703" data-end="743">
<p data-start="705" data-end="743">Double-click your HTML file to open it</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1itptxb" data-start="744" data-end="762">
<p data-start="746" data-end="762">Refresh the page</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="764" data-end="813">👉 You should now see the mascot on the top right</p>
<hr data-start="815" data-end="818">
<h1 data-section-id="6dru9n" data-start="820" data-end="845">❗ If it DOESN’T show up</h1>
<p data-start="846" data-end="875">Here are the 3 common issues:</p>
<ul data-start="876" data-end="994">
<li data-section-id="137ewo7" data-start="876" data-end="927">
<p data-start="878" data-end="927">File name is wrong (must be exactly <code data-start="914" data-end="926">mascot.png</code>)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="a7pohu" data-start="928" data-end="967">
<p data-start="930" data-end="967">It saved as <code data-start="942" data-end="948">.jpg</code> or <code data-start="952" data-end="959">.webp</code> instead</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="c3b9sk" data-start="968" data-end="994">
<p data-start="970" data-end="994">It’s in the wrong folder</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="996" data-end="999">
<p data-start="1001" data-end="1030">If you want, you can tell me:</p>
<ul data-start="1031" data-end="1075">
<li data-section-id="1qq80jf" data-start="1031" data-end="1075">
<p data-start="1033" data-end="1075">what device you’re on (Mac, Windows, etc.)</p>
</li>
</ul>
